    "This test, relying on ranked data to compute an H-statistic, evaluates variations between groups.",
    "Surprisingly, the test yielded an H-statistic of 16.9751, corresponding p-value of 0.0019, indicating significant differences among the groups.Following the Kruskal-Wallis test, we conducted a Dunn's test [45] using the Bonferroni [46] correction to explore specific disparities among these groups.",
    "The resulting matrix of p-values (Table 3) from Dunn's test highlights a significant difference between the BDA and WDA methods; the rest of the methods as we expected does not have a significant difference to locate nuclei.",
    "Values of 1 along the diagonal signify comparisons of the same groups, indicating no significant differences.",
    "Conversely, lower p-values off the diagonal signify notable distinctions between specific pairs of groups."
